NAME
    file - determine file type

SYNOPSIS
    file [options] <file...>

DESCRIPTION
    Determines file type by examining file name extension and
    content. Reports type description or MIME type.

OPTIONS
    -b              Brief mode (no filename in output)
    -i              Output MIME type instead of description
    -L              Follow symbolic links

FILE TYPES
    Detected types include:
    - JSON, XML, YAML, TOML data
    - HTML, CSS, Markdown documents
    - JavaScript, TypeScript source
    - Shell scripts
    - Images (PNG, JPEG, GIF, SVG)
    - Archives (ZIP, gzip, tar)
    - SQLite databases
    - Plain text and binary data

EXAMPLES
    file config.json
        config.json: JSON data

    file -i config.json
        config.json: application/json

    file -b *
        JSON data
        directory
        ASCII text

    file /api/data/users/123
        /api/data/users/123: JSON data

SEE ALSO
    stat, ls
